In this article, it is mentioned that President Trump has emphasized the need to end Chain Migration as part of any deal on DACA. Chain Migration refers to the current system in which newcomers are admitted to the United States based on family ties, rather than a merit-based system that considers economic and national security factors. The article highlights the fiscal and national security consequences of a large influx of predominantly low-skilled migrants. It also suggests that understanding the scale of the challenge posed by Chain Migration is important for those responsible for the nation's checks and screening processes.